        "id": 5045
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-04-18T15:52:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m saying the reason we have the bytesUsed() method is to track what you\u0027re calling (bytes used + overhead + waste).  It\u0027s all the bytes we use, whether or not productively.\n\nIf you allocate an array of N Ts where sizeof(T) \u003c alignof(T), you need to allocate N*alignof(T) bytes.  N*sizeof(T) bytes + alignof(T) doesn\u0027t allow you to align the internal Ts.",
      "parentUuid": "27a4f40b_2ed5a96b",
